obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (43930)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00044_188207_1523272415955&sectionId=43930&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00044_188207_1523272415955
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `This Act may be called the Powers-of-Attorney Act, 1882.`
  line
  line `Local extent.---It applies to the whole of India ^1***;`
  line
  line `Commencement.--- and it shall come into force on the first day of May, 1882.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1.The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth`
  line `Schedule (w.e.f. 31-10-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_1_a:
  sectionId (43931)
  sectionNo 1A
  orderNo 2
  title Definition.
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 55 of 1982, s. 2 (w.e.f. 22-10-1980).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00044_188207_1523272415955&sectionId=43931&sectionno=1A&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00044_188207_1523272415955
obj_root_law_sections_1_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[1A. Definition.--In this Act, "power-of-attorney" includes any instrument empowering`
  line `a specified person to act for and in the name of the person executing it.]`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (43932)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 3
  title `Execution under power-of-attorney.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1 The word "assurance" omitted by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 22-10-1980).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00044_188207_1523272415955&sectionId=43932&sectionno=2&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00044_188207_1523272415955
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `The donee of a power-of-attorney may, if he`
  line `thinks fit, execute or do any ^1*** instrument or thing in and with his own name and signature,`
  line `and his own seal, where sealing is required, by the authority of the donor of the power; and`
  line `every ^1*** instrument and thing so executed and done, shall be as effectual in law as if it had`
  line `been executed or done by the donee of the power in the name, and with the signature and seal,`
  line `of the donor thereof.`
  line
  line `This section applies to powers-of-attorney created by instruments executed either before or after this`
  line `Act comes into force.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (43933)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 4
  title `Payment by attorney under power, without notice of death, etc., good.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00044_188207_1523272415955&sectionId=43933&sectionno=3&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00044_188207_1523272415955
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `Any person`
  line `making or doing any payment or act in good faith, in pursuance of a power-of-attorney, shall not`
  line `be liable in respect of the payment or act by reason that, before the payment or act, the donor of`
  line `the power had died or become ^1*** of unsound mind, ^2*** or insolvent, or had revoked the`
  line `power, if the fact of death, ^3*** unsoundness of mind, ^4*** insolvency or revocation was not, at`
  line `the time of the payment or act, known to the person making or doing the same.`
  line
  line `But this section shall not affect any right against the payee of any person interested in any`
  line `money so paid; and that person shall have the like remedy against the payee as he would have`
  line `had against the payer, if the payment had not been made by him.`
  line
  line `This section applies only to payments and acts made or done after this Act comes into force.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The word "lunatic," omitted by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 22-10-1980).`
  line
  line `2. The word "or bankrupt" omitted by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 22-10-1980).`
  line
  line `3. The word "lunacy," omitted by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 22-10-1980).`
  line
  line `4. The word "bankruptcy," omitted by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 22-10-1980).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (43934)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 5
  title `Deposit of original instruments creating powers-of-attorney.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00044_188207_1523272415955&sectionId=43934&sectionno=4&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00044_188207_1523272415955
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(a) An instrument`
  line `creating a power-of-attorney, its execution being verified by affidavit, statutory declaration or`
  line `other sufficient evidence, may, with the affidavit or declaration, if any, be deposited in the High`
  line `Court ^1[or District Court] within the local limits of whose jurisdiction the instrument may be.`
  line
  line `(b) A separate file of instruments so deposited shall be kept; and any person may search that`
  line `file, and inspect every instrument so deposited; and a certified copy thereof shall be delivered`
  line `out to him on request.`
  line
  line `(c) A copy of an instrument so deposited may be presented at the office and may be stamped`
  line `or marked as a certified copy, and, when so stamped or marked, shall become and be a certified`
  line copy.
  line
  line `(d) A certified copy of an instrument so deposited shall, without further proof, be sufficient`
  line `evidence of the contents of the instrument and of the deposit thereof in the High Court ^2[District Court].`
  line
  line `(e) The High Court may, from time to time, make rules for the purposes of this section, and`
  line `prescribing, with the concurrence of the State Government, the fees to be taken under clauses (a), (b)`
  line `and (c).`
  line
  line `^3** * * *`
  line
  line `(g) This section applies to instruments creating powers-of-attorney executed either before or after this`
  line `Act comes into force.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Ins. by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 22-10-1980).`
  line
  line `2 . Ins. by Act 55 of 1982, s. 5.`
  line
  line `3. Clause (f) rep. Act 6 of 1900, s. 48 and the Second Schedule`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (43935)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 6
  title `Power-of-attorney of married women.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 55 of 1982, s. 6, for certain words (w.e.f. 22-10-1982).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00044_188207_1523272415955&sectionId=43935&sectionno=5&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00044_188207_1523272415955
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `^1[A married woman of full age shall, by virtue of this`
  line `Act, have power, as if she were unmarried,] by a non-testamentary instrument, to appoint an attorney on`
  line `her behalf, for the purpose of executing any non-testamentary instrument or doing any other act which she`
  line `might herself execute or do; and the provisions of this Act, relating to instruments creating powers-ofattorney, shall apply thereto.`
  line
  line `This section applies only to instruments executed after this Act comes into force.`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (43936)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 7
  title [Repealed.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00044_188207_1523272415955&sectionId=43936&sectionno=6&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00044_188207_1523272415955
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `[Act 28 of 1866, section 39 repealed.] Rep. by the Amending Act, 1891 (12 of 1891),`
  line `s. 2 and the First Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
